{"id": "85", "instruction": "Let $n (n \\geq 3)$ be the order of matrix $A=\\left( \\begin{matrix} {{{{1}}}} & {{{{a}}}} & {{{{\\mathrm{L}}}}} & {{{{a}}}} \\\\ {{{{a}}}} & {{{{1}}}} & {{{{\\mathrm{L}}}}} & {{{{a}}}} \\\\ {{{{\\mathrm{M}}}}} & {{{{\\mathrm{M}}}}} & {{{{\\mathrm{M}}}}} \\\\ {{{{a}}}} & {{{{a}}}} & {{{{\\mathrm{L}}}}} & {{{{1}}}} \\\\ \\end{matrix} \\right)$ , what is the value of $\\left| A \\right|$?\n\nOptions:\nA. $$\\left| A \\right|=[ -1+( n-1 ) a ] ( 1-a )^{n-1}\n$$\nB. $$\\left| A \\right|=[ 4+( n-1 ) a ] ( 1-a )^{n-1}\n$$\nC. $$\\left| A \\right|=[ 1+( n+1 ) a ] ( 1-a )^{n-1}\n$$\nD. $$\\left| A \\right|=[ 1-( n-1 ) a ] ( 1-a )^{n-1}\n$$\nE. $$\\left| A \\right|=[ 1+( n-1 ) a ] ( 1-a )^{n+1}\n$$\nF. $$\\left| A \\right|=[ 1+( n-1 ) a ] ( 1+a )^{n-1}\n$$\nG. $$\\left| A \\right|=[ 3+( n-1 ) a ] ( 1-a )^{n-1}\n$$\nH. $$\\left| A \\right|=[ 2+( n-1 ) a ] ( 1-a )^{n-1}\n$$\nI. $$\\left| A \\right|=[ 5+( n-1 ) a ] ( 1-a )^{n-1}\n$$\nJ. $$\\left| A \\right|=[ 1+( n-1 ) a ] ( 1-a )^{n-1}\n$$", "output": "J"}
